{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Psychic|type2=Fairy}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Kirlia}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Psychic|prevnum=280|prev=Ralts|nextnum=282|next=Gardevoir|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Kirlia}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Kirlia\n|jname=キルリア\n|jtranslit=Kiruria\n|tmname=Kirlia\n|ndex=281\n|hdex=030\n|sdex=158\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=065\n|fbrow=027\n|abrow=158\n|obrow=134\n|opbrow=193\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Psychic\n|type2=Fairy\n|category=Emotion\n|height-ftin=2\'07"\n|height-m=0.8\n|weight-lbs=44.5\n|weight-kg=20.2\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Synchronize\n|ability2=Trace\n|abilityd=Telepathy\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Amorphous\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evsa=2\n|expyield=97\n|oldexp=140\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=White\n|catchrate=120\n|body=12\n|pokefordex=kirlia\n|generation=3\n|friendship=35\n}}\n\'\'\'Kirlia\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'キルリア\'\'\' \'\'Kirlia\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Psychic|Fairy}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]]. Prior to Generation VI, it was a pure {{type|Psychic}} Pokémon.\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Ralts}} starting at [[level]] 20 and evolves into {{p|Gardevoir}} starting at level 30 or, if male, into {{p|Gallade}} when exposed to a [[Dawn Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\nKirlia is a bipedal, humanoid Pokémon that appears to be wearing a tutu. Most of its body is white, and there are three ruffles on each hip. Beneath the ruffles, it has skinny green legs with long, pointed feet. Its arms are also thin with two digits each. It has green hair that covers most of its face and reaches its shoulders on either side, resembling two {{wp|ponytail}}s. Large, red eyes are visible on either side of the hair that covers its face. On each side of its head is a flat, red horn that resembles a hairpin.\n\nKirlia\'s horns are used to amplify its psychokinetic power and distort the air around it. The distortion in the air causes scenery mirages and can cause a rip in dimensions. This ability also allows this Pokémon to see into the future. It enjoys dancing on sunny mornings, and grows beautiful when exposed to a {{pkmn|Trainer}} with positive emotions. Kirlia inhabits {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Urban Pokémon|urban areas}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Nebel Plateau Kirlia.png|thumb|250px|left|Kirlia in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nKirlia debuted in \'\'[[M06|Jirachi: Wish Maker]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Butler]]. It was used for a magic act during the [[Millennium Festival]], and later to fight an {{p|Absol}}.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[AG086|Lights, Camerupt, Action!]]\'\'. [[Elijah]] used a Kirlia in a movie where it played the {{wp|damsel in distress}} in the movie, being taken by an {{p|Exploud}} and later rescued by {{p|Plusle}} and {{p|Minun}}.\n\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[AG109|Do I Hear a Ralts?]]\'\' along with a Gardevoir. Both of them sent {{TRT}} flying when they cornered [[Max]] and {{AP|Snorunt}} while they were hurrying to send Ralts to the [[Pokémon Center]]. However, Kirlia and Gardevoir thought that Max was also trying to steal Ralts. When Ralts blocked Kirlia and Gardevoir\'s {{m|Psychic}}, all hostilities were ignored and the two Pokémon left. Kirlia and Gardevoir appeared once more at the near-end of the episode to send [[James]] flying as Ralts had already launched [[Jessie]] and {{MTR}} for posing as Gardevoir and Kirlia.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[AG146|Fear Factor Phony]]\'\' as a resident of an abandoned mining colony. [[Jessie\'s Wobbuffet]] fell in love with the Emotion Pokémon.\n\nTwo Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[DP020|Mutiny in the Bounty!]]\'\'. One appeared in a flashback, being one of [[Pokémon poacher|Pokémon Hunter]] [[J]]\'s stolen Pokémon. The other was used by [[Melodi]] so Ash and {{ashfr}} could find out where J and [[J\'s henchmen|her minions]] will strike next, after [[Ash\'s Pikachu]], Melodi\'s Gardevoir, and Team Rocket\'s Meowth were all stolen.\n\nA male Kirlia appeared  in \'\'[[DP155|Double-Time Battle Training!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Zoey]]. She used him, along with her {{p|Leafeon}}, in a [[Double Battle]] against [[Dawn\'s Cyndaquil]] and {{TP|Dawn|Mamoswine}}. He was later shown to have evolved into a {{p|Gallade}} in \'\'[[DP177|A Grand Fight for Winning!]]\'\'.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nKirlia made its main series debut in a flashback in \'\'[[AG060|Delcatty Got Your Tongue]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Coordinator}}. It was defeated by [[Dr. Abby]]\'s {{p|Skitty}} during the [[Contest Battle|Battle Stage]] of the [[Grand Festival]].\n\nA Coordinator\'s Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[AG167|What I Did for Love!]]\'\'.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in [[Jessie]]\'s fantasy in \'\'[[AG168|Three Jynx and a Baby!]]\'\'.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon attacked by {{OBP|Darkrai|M10}} and having nightmares. [[Alicia]], [[Alice]]\'s grandmother, treated Kirlia and woke it up, along with {{p|Roserade}} and {{p|Luxray}}.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[M16|Genesect and the Legend Awakened]]\'\' as a resident of [[Pokémon Hills]].\n\nA Kirlia appeared in [[BWS01]].\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[XY002|Lumiose City Pursuit!]]\'\'.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[XY008|Grooming Furfrou!]]\'\'\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[XY026|A Battle by Any Other Name!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Performer}}\'s Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[XY060|A Showcase Debut!]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the [[Coumarine City]] [[Pokémon Showcase]].\n\nTwo Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[XY092|Cloudy Fate, Bright Future!]]\'\'. One was under the ownership of a {{tc|Psychic}}, while the other was owned by a Trainer.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[XY105|Party Dancecapades!]]\'\', under the ownership of a Performer attending [[Monsieur Pierre]]\'s dance party.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\nA Kirlia appeared during a flashback in \'\'[[SM113|This Magik Moment!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Kirlia appeared in [[SM141]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP020|Kirlia|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Kirlia, the Emotion Pokémon. Kirlia uses the horns on its head to amplify its Psychic powers, and when this occurs reality becomes warped, and future events can be seen.}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP155|Kirlia|Ash\'s Pokédex|Kirlia, the Emotion Pokémon. Kirlia is able to sense the feelings of its Trainer, and when it becomes happy, it will start to dance.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Kirlia PMRS.png|thumb|200px|Kirlia in [[Pokémon Ruby-Sapphire]]]]\n[[File:Rara Kirlia.png|thumb|200px|Kirlia in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the movie adaptations===\nA Kirlia appeared in {{ma|Genesect and the Legend Awakened}}.\n\nA Kirlia appeared in the {{ma|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel|manga adaptation}} of \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\n===In the Pokémon + Nobunaga\'s Ambition ~ Ranse\'s Color Picture Scroll ~ manga===\n[[Kanetsugu]] owns a Kirlia.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Rara}}\n{{adv|Ruby}} has a {{p|Ralts}} that evolved into a Kirlia, [[nickname]]d Rara. While he was with {{adv|Wally}}, Wally wound up keeping Rara (then still a Ralts) after an earthquake separated Ruby and Wally. In \'\'[[PS241|Prior to Rayquaza Redemption I]]\'\', she evolved into Kirlia. Rara was returned to Ruby when he met up with Wally again. In the \'\'[[Omega Ruby & Alpha Sapphire chapter (Adventures)|Omega Ruby & Alpha Sapphire chapter]]\'\', Rara evolved into a {{p|Gardevoir}} while under {{adv|Sapphire}}\'s {{pkmn|training}}.\n\nA Kirlia {{pkmn2|caught}} by {{adv|Crystal}} and lent to {{adv|Emerald}} for his [[Battle Pike]] challenge appeared in \'\'[[PS309|Moving Past Milotic]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[PAORAS00|Omega Alpha Adventure 0]]\'\', {{adv|Sapphire}} is revealed to have obtained a male Kirlia, nicknamed Kirly. In the same chapter, Kirly evolved into {{p|Gallade}} when Sapphire accidentally unearthed a [[Dawn Stone]] and kicked it towards him.\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\nA {{tc|Battle Girl}} used a Kirlia against [[Hareta]] in \'\'[[DPA25|Clash! Hareta vs. Koya]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon + Nobunaga\'s Ambition ~ Ranse\'s Color Picture Scroll ~ manga===\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[PNA2|The Green Scroll: Kenshin\'s Adventure]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Kanetsugu]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\nA Kirlia appeared in \'\'[[PMRS29|Rare Pokémon!!]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Kirlia (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Psychic|type2=Fairy}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=030|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=It is said that a Kirlia that is exposed to the positive emotions of its {{pkmn|Trainer}} grows beautiful. This Pokémon controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Kirlia uses the horns on its head to amplify its psychokinetic power. When the Pokémon uses its power, the air around it becomes distorted, creating mirages of nonexistent scenery.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Emerald|t=FFF|entry=A Kirlia has the psychic power to create a rip in the dimensions and see into the future. It is said to dance with pleasure on sunny mornings.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=FireRed|v2=LeafGreen|entry=The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=158|label1={{gameabbrev4|Pt}}:|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Diamond|v2=Pearl|entry=It is highly perceptive of its Trainer\'s feelings. It dances when it is feeling happy.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=If its Trainer becomes h